Pray more.

00:31:03.137 --> 00:31:07.040
Come up to my throne more.

00:31:07.040 --> 00:31:11.520
Have more fellowship with me more in the throne room.

00:31:19.286 --> 00:31:19.537
" And as people were rowing this boat, we were all working together with one heart in one accord.

00:31:19.537 --> 00:31:35.800
Just like it was with the upper room: they come with a sound of a mighty rushing wind, but first they were all in one accord.

00:31:46.720 --> 00:31:47.206
They were all praying and they were in one accord.

00:31:55.360 --> 00:31:56.000
And then boom, it came a sound.

00:31:56.000 --> 00:32:01.457
Boom, the Holy Ghost and fire came.

00:32:01.457 --> 00:32:05.727
Boom, speaking in tongues.

00:32:05.727 --> 00:32:08.720
Boom, all this stuff happened.

00:32:08.720 --> 00:32:12.432
Look what God did.

00:32:24.846 --> 00:32:33.440
I see that as where we are right now with all of us coming together and boom, here we are and the glory of the Lord as we are rowing this boat in this end-time army, praying forth everything he has for us to do.

00:32:33.720 --> 00:32:42.520
And I was looking for scripture, and remember I told you all about I saw the babies and they were coming back to the churches.

00:32:42.520 --> 00:32:48.827
Now I'm not talking about everybody's going to go back to the church where they came from if it's a corrupt church.

00:32:50.967 --> 00:32:57.300
I'm talking about you had some kind of silly difference and you probably don't even...

00:32:57.300 --> 00:33:09.960
if you really stopped and thought about it and you said, "Brandon, I don't remember why I left.

00:33:09.960 --> 00:33:16.766
I have to really think about it.

00:33:18.640 --> 00:33:18.910
Why did I leave that church?

00:33:18.910 --> 00:33:20.800
What was I mad about?

00:33:20.800 --> 00:33:23.215
What was I irritated about?

00:33:23.215 --> 00:33:24.460
Was there really something there?

00:33:26.600 --> 00:33:43.287
" And you really can't even give me a real reason why when the Lord assigned you there other than you just were irritated and, "Well, you know what?

00:33:44.840 --> 00:33:51.206
I didn't like the way he preached, so I got out of there.

00:33:51.206 --> 00:33:54.387
" But you know, God called you there.

00:33:54.387 --> 00:33:55.740
That's who I'm talking about.

00:33:55.740 --> 00:34:05.720
Not some kind of scandal where the pastor was doing something bad or whatever and you're like, "I'm out of here.

00:34:09.013 --> 00:34:14.810
" I'm talking about where you know that God had called you there and you still inside of you know there's something there.

00:34:14.810 --> 00:34:18.857
The Holy Spirit's warning you; he's stirring in you.

00:34:18.857 --> 00:34:20.759
That's what I'm talking about.

00:34:20.759 --> 00:34:30.480
But he gave me Psalms 92:13 and 14: "Those that be planted in the house of the Lord shall flourish in the courts of our God.

00:34:30.480 --> 00:34:37.919
They shall still bring forth fruit in old age; they shall be fat and flourishing.

00:34:40.899 --> 00:34:41.239
" Because they were rooted.

00:34:41.239 --> 00:35:00.091
And as they are fat and flourishing in the spirit because they are bringing forth great fruit in old age, they're fat and flourishing because they didn't let offense bother them.

00:35:00.091 --> 00:35:30.760
They didn't allow the rumor mill from Sister Clipboard to tick them off and say, "Well, Sister Clipboard, I heard from the other Sister Clipboard and that Sister Clipboard was talking to that Sister Clipboard, and everybody sitting there being a busybody, and they got over here to you and you heard about what she said...

00:35:30.760 --> 00:35:46.331
" And relay telephone that came out that I said the color purple and you said it was something else and you don't even know what was said.

00:36:00.566 --> 00:36:00.880
And the next thing you know, "I'm gone.

00:36:00.880 --> 00:36:02.840
Well, I'm out of here.

00:36:03.338 --> 00:36:05.780
I already thought there might be something going on here.

00:36:05.780 --> 00:36:07.010
I'm out of here.

00:36:07.010 --> 00:36:09.290
" That's what I'm talking about.

00:36:09.290 --> 00:36:24.951
But the ones that are fat and they're full of fruit—those that be planted in the house of the Lord—we're planted in the church, in the house of the Lord.

00:36:24.951 --> 00:36:26.258
We're there.

00:36:26.258 --> 00:36:27.564
We're planted.

00:36:27.564 --> 00:36:28.480
Shall flourish.

00:36:28.480 --> 00:36:29.920
We're going to flourish.

00:36:29.920 --> 00:36:34.773
It didn't say we're going to barely get by.

00:36:34.773 --> 00:36:40.540
That's why the Bible said that the willing and obedient will eat the good of the land.

00:36:48.373 --> 00:36:54.875
If you're not eating the good of the land and you're struggling and barely getting by, check your willingness and how obedient you were.

00:36:54.875 --> 00:36:56.200
Are you willing?

00:37:17.680 --> 00:37:18.757
It's not just about you doing something; are you willing and obedient?

00:37:22.808 --> 00:37:23.136
So, check your willingness.

00:37:23.136 --> 00:37:24.577
Check your thermostat.

00:37:24.577 --> 00:37:27.037
Am I willing and obedient?

00:37:27.037 --> 00:37:32.124
Do I qualify to eat the good of the land?

00:37:33.547 --> 00:37:38.455
The Bible says the willing and obedient will eat the good of the land.

00:37:38.455 --> 00:37:47.651
And I have to say, you look at yourself and say, "Am I eating the good of the land?

00:37:47.651 --> 00:37:49.752
" What does that mean?

00:37:49.752 --> 00:37:51.416
Because the Bible said we could.

00:37:51.416 --> 00:38:01.560
So, how is it when a lot of people say, "Well, I'm struggling.

00:38:06.348 --> 00:38:06.576
I got this"?

00:38:06.576 --> 00:38:07.944
Well, check your thermostat.

00:38:07.944 --> 00:38:12.891
Am I willing and obedient to what God has called me to do?

00:38:26.920 --> 00:38:27.100
But a lot of it is that a lot of people have misplaced themselves.

00:38:31.493 --> 00:38:36.240
You say, "Well, God called you to give to a certain ministry, to a certain church, and you didn't like it.

00:38:36.240 --> 00:38:37.200
Well, I'm out of here.

00:38:37.200 --> 00:38:41.500
" Well, I go back to being willing and obedient.

00:38:41.500 --> 00:38:46.175
What did God tell you to do?

00:39:06.756 --> 00:39:06.933
Not everything is always going to be appeasing to your flesh.

00:39:06.933 --> 00:39:10.143
So, I check myself all the time.

00:39:10.143 --> 00:39:11.412
Am I willing and obedient?

00:39:11.412 --> 00:39:15.920
Because those that are planted in the house of the Lord shall flourish in the courts of our God.

00:39:15.920 --> 00:39:20.937
I'm going to flourish; I'm going to be filled with and controlled by the Holy Ghost.

00:39:20.937 --> 00:39:24.690
Even whenever I get offended, I sow seed.

00:39:24.690 --> 00:39:32.640
Even whenever I get annoyed, I say, "Here, let me bless you.

00:39:32.640 --> 00:39:35.080
Bless those.

00:39:35.080 --> 00:39:37.840
" You've got to come up higher.

00:39:54.080 --> 00:39:54.324
And it's not all the time you know your flesh wants to do that.

00:40:04.377 --> 00:40:04.606
Well, be willing and obedient.

00:40:07.400 --> 00:40:08.810
So I always say, check where you're planted.

00:40:08.810 --> 00:40:11.240
Where are you going to church?

00:40:11.240 --> 00:40:18.110
Where are you in your fellowship with the Lord?

00:40:18.110 --> 00:40:23.250
Are you going from church to church trying to find a perfect church?

00:40:23.250 --> 00:40:27.555
Because I'm going to tell you, there is no perfect church.

00:40:39.010 --> 00:40:39.215
There is no perfect pastor.

00:40:39.215 --> 00:40:40.969
There is no perfect pastor's wife.

00:40:40.969 --> 00:40:42.417
There's no perfect deacon board.

00:40:42.417 --> 00:40:46.966
If you have a deacon board, everybody has issues.

00:40:46.966 --> 00:40:51.685
Everybody has something they're going through.

00:40:51.685 --> 00:40:57.520
We're all a work in progress, going from glory to glory.

00:40:57.520 --> 00:41:13.142
But I'm trying to clean up the church right now, telling you the willing and obedient will eat the good of the land.

00:41:28.311 --> 00:41:28.507
And I have to check my thermostat.

00:41:28.507 --> 00:41:30.791
Am I eating the good of the land?

00:41:42.480 --> 00:41:42.760
Is God taking care of me?

00:41:42.760 --> 00:41:44.440
Is everything going well?

00:41:44.440 --> 00:41:48.107
Is my thermostat right with him all the time?

00:41:48.107 --> 00:41:50.223
You have to check it.

00:41:50.775 --> 00:41:51.795
Where are you sowing?

00:41:59.560 --> 00:41:59.815
Where are you giving your tithes and your offerings?

00:41:59.815 --> 00:42:01.345
Check where you're giving.

00:42:01.345 --> 00:42:04.800
You have to do that all the time.

00:42:15.760 --> 00:42:16.165
I do it, Lord; I measure it.

00:42:19.000 --> 00:42:24.531
And when you're like a farmer that plants, you expect hundredfold, right?

00:42:24.531 --> 00:42:28.657
A farmer always knows this is where I want to plant.

00:42:28.657 --> 00:42:35.600
I'm going to sow my seed in this field, and it's either good manure or it's bad soil.

00:42:35.600 --> 00:42:44.440
But I know that this soil is rich, and if I plant corn, I'm going to get a bumper crop.

00:42:59.613 --> 00:42:59.787
So I always measure it out.

00:42:59.787 --> 00:43:00.827
What makes soil good?

00:43:00.827 --> 00:43:02.571
What makes soil rich?

00:43:02.571 --> 00:43:09.242
What makes some thirty, some sixty, and a hundredfold?

00:43:09.242 --> 00:43:11.945
What makes it where some seed doesn't produce at all?

00:43:11.945 --> 00:43:13.373
Well, bad soil.

00:43:13.373 --> 00:43:17.140
It's not hard, but we make it hard.

00:43:17.140 --> 00:43:21.176
We try to make everything so super spiritual.

00:43:21.176 --> 00:43:26.154
We say, "Well, we've got to fast and pray.

00:43:26.154 --> 00:43:42.015
" I'm not knocking fasting and praying, but I get tired of the excuse where everybody puts up the spiritual wall and they try to make a mountain out of a molehill.

00:43:42.015 --> 00:43:46.980
Thirty, sixty, hundredfold is when you realize where your sowing is.

00:43:53.869 --> 00:43:54.263
Is there fruit there?

00:43:54.263 --> 00:43:56.196
Do you see it?

00:44:04.013 --> 00:44:04.467
And I know a lot of people criticize megachurches.

00:44:04.467 --> 00:44:11.400
They criticize things, and God gives the sheep to the people he can trust.

00:44:11.400 --> 00:44:32.496
I'm not always saying everyone's right in the mega church, but I would say a lot of times when you see it, they're nurturing those babies and bringing them up and at least teaching them something, versus some people that don't.

00:44:32.496 --> 00:44:35.125
How do you handle what God has given you?

00:44:35.125 --> 00:44:40.817
The Bible says, "Be faithful over little and he'll make you ruler over much.

00:44:40.817 --> 00:44:45.434
" But people don't want to be faithful over the little God's given them.

00:44:52.120 --> 00:44:52.450
And God's not going to let you beat the sheep.

00:44:52.450 --> 00:44:56.840
God's not going to let you beat people.

00:44:56.840 --> 00:45:00.200
He's going to make sure you're treating them right.

00:45:00.200 --> 00:45:04.533
And a lot of people don't want to hear that.

00:45:04.533 --> 00:45:10.040
That's why: be faithful over little; he'll make you ruler over much.

00:45:10.040 --> 00:45:14.274
How do you handle the sheep God has given you?

00:45:19.120 --> 00:45:19.667
And so I see and I watch it.

00:45:24.800 --> 00:45:25.920
And as a watchman, I see a lot more than I say.

00:45:27.609 --> 00:45:29.031
I just sit and I listen.

00:45:29.031 --> 00:45:32.050
And the Lord gives me discernment each day.

00:45:32.050 --> 00:45:35.355
It's not always for you to call it out.

00:45:35.355 --> 00:45:38.937
It's none of your business; he didn't ask you to do it.

00:45:38.937 --> 00:45:45.320
A lot of times he's only sent me to a couple of churches and I sat in the back.

00:45:45.320 --> 00:45:47.780
And the pastor ran back and said, "Who are you?

00:45:48.150 --> 00:45:52.935
" I said, "The Lord told me judgment's coming to your church.

00:46:07.743 --> 00:46:08.017
" And they look at me and go, "Okay.

00:46:08.017 --> 00:46:11.300
" Like he wants me to leave now.

00:46:13.171 --> 00:46:13.366
But guess what?

00:46:13.366 --> 00:46:15.967
Six months later, they're closed.

00:46:15.967 --> 00:46:20.880
Just like the Lord said, you warn people, and you just keep pushing.

00:46:22.800 --> 00:46:24.592
I don't have everything always perfect, but I keep pushing.

00:46:24.592 --> 00:46:25.168
I'm trying.

00:46:25.168 --> 00:46:27.389
We're getting weight off.

00:46:27.389 --> 00:46:29.480
We're working out.

00:46:29.480 --> 00:46:30.760
We're exercising.

00:46:30.760 --> 00:46:37.060
We're walking around, and I count my steps every day.

00:46:37.365 --> 00:46:40.400
You know what I'm trying to say.

00:46:40.400 --> 00:46:41.480
They say 10,000 steps.

00:46:41.480 --> 00:46:43.400
I'm like, "Oh my gosh, how many steps is that?

00:46:43.400 --> 00:46:48.325
" They said, "Well, I believe it's 2,000 steps per mile.

00:46:48.325 --> 00:46:55.675
" So, I've been walking and doing my steps and trying to make sure the flesh...

00:47:02.131 --> 00:47:02.674
and the older you get, the more it's been exciting.

00:47:02.674 --> 00:47:13.800
Tonight I had salad and they're all eating birthday cake and I was sitting there looking at them going, "This is terrible.

00:47:31.710 --> 00:47:31.945
" I told Braden, I said, "How's that cake taste, boy?

00:47:31.945 --> 00:47:34.800
" He goes, "You know, Dad, it wasn't that good.

00:47:34.800 --> 00:47:38.220
Don't worry about it.

00:47:38.955 --> 00:47:41.160
" I said, "It looked good to me.

00:47:44.845 --> 00:47:45.050
" It was from Cheesecake Factory.

00:47:45.870 --> 00:47:48.171
I said, "Oh, I wanted some so bad.

00:47:48.171 --> 00:47:55.560
" I was there looking at that and Megan had her hands all in it and she's licking her hands.

00:47:56.520 --> 00:47:59.512
I said, "Oh, Jesus, take the wheel.

00:48:01.937 --> 00:48:02.743
" I said, "But that's okay, baby.

00:48:02.743 --> 00:48:04.600
Enjoy that birthday cake.

00:48:04.600 --> 00:48:14.380
Daddy will just eat a piece of celery and watch you and pretend I'm eating it.

00:48:14.380 --> 00:48:17.216
" But I made it.

00:48:18.920 --> 00:48:19.140
I got through it.

00:48:19.140 --> 00:48:22.394
It's not always easy.

00:48:22.394 --> 00:48:23.680
What's that?

00:48:31.360 --> 00:48:31.653
The Cheeto guy.

00:48:31.653 --> 00:48:33.707
It's not easy being cheesy.

00:48:33.707 --> 00:48:35.200
Let's pray.

00:48:35.200 --> 00:48:37.440
I'm just trying to warn you of what the Holy Spirit's telling me.

00:48:42.280 --> 00:48:42.787
You say, "Well, Brandon, I don't believe anything you said.

00:48:42.787 --> 00:48:43.463
" That's fine.

00:48:43.463 --> 00:48:45.560
I'm not here to convince you of anything.

00:48:45.560 --> 00:48:52.070
I'm here to keep warning, beating my drum, doing what I feel the Lord's called me to do.

00:49:01.840 --> 00:49:02.034
And if you don't like what I'm saying...

00:49:07.668 --> 00:49:07.896
I get the letters in the mail.

00:49:12.480 --> 00:49:12.860
I get the emails.

00:49:12.860 --> 00:49:29.080
People don't like it; people telling me they believe we're going through the whole tribulation and writing me a whole book of how I'm so wrong in teaching all of you that I believe that the rapture of the church is about to happen.

00:49:29.080 --> 00:49:41.190
Then I have people say that there are all these different things and different theologies, and I say, "Where did they come up with this stuff?

00:49:41.190 --> 00:49:49.729
" Some YouTube people say, "I believe it this way.

00:50:07.829 --> 00:50:08.206
" I say, "I don't see where that's in the Bible.

00:50:10.048 --> 00:50:16.347
" And I talk to the elders and they think they're crazy and they say, "Well, that's fine.

00:50:16.347 --> 00:50:18.960
" Everybody has a different way they interpret scripture.

00:50:18.960 --> 00:50:19.800
They do.

00:50:19.800 --> 00:50:23.380
So, I'm not here to argue theology with people.

00:50:23.380 --> 00:50:30.765
I try to follow people like Rick Renner and Billye Brim and Perry Stone, people that have some Greek study mixed in there.

00:50:36.833 --> 00:50:47.818
You can listen to what they're saying with the scripture and they add it and they put it together and I look and I go, "That makes sense.

00:50:47.818 --> 00:50:55.640
" Put the Greek with the King James and I go, "Okay, I get it.

00:50:55.640 --> 00:51:03.320
" Some people are so over my head I go, "Man, I got to hear that seven times.

00:51:09.360 --> 00:51:09.651
" You know Charles Capps was a good one, too.

00:51:16.600 --> 00:51:16.760
He taught the end times well, and Hilton Sutton.

00:51:35.920 --> 00:51:36.133
But what I understood is that some of these big Bible teachers that taught that stuff didn't always agree with each other.

00:51:36.133 --> 00:51:44.380
And so this one taught that one, but they were friends and they agreed to disagree.

00:51:44.380 --> 00:51:49.160
They didn't beat each other down.

00:51:49.160 --> 00:51:52.800
They just kept walking.

00:51:52.800 --> 00:51:55.000
None of them are here.

00:51:55.000 --> 00:52:03.080
They all went home to be with the Lord, but they loved each other and they got along.

00:52:03.080 --> 00:52:04.885
People weren't in strife.

00:52:04.885 --> 00:52:09.260
Like I said, you can agree to disagree without having to be mean.

00:52:09.260 --> 00:52:12.360
So that's what I've learned with end-time theology.

00:52:18.424 --> 00:52:20.188
I just stay in my lane and try to just say what the Lord has told me to say.

00:52:20.188 --> 00:52:27.250
Now I've been reading John Bevere's book, 'The King is Coming,' A+.

00:52:27.250 --> 00:52:30.680
He believes what I believe.

00:52:30.680 --> 00:52:34.246
There is a rapture of the church.

00:52:47.960 --> 00:52:48.353
He believes it.

00:52:48.353 --> 00:52:50.850
And I believe it, too.

00:52:50.850 --> 00:53:02.710
And I think anybody that's been in my circle, you know, with Rick Renner and all these people, they all believe it—that Jesus is coming sooner than later.

00:53:04.440 --> 00:53:20.280
All I want to tell you every single time I come on here is that if you don't get anything else, you need to know there's a heaven to gain and a hell to shun.

00:53:20.280 --> 00:53:26.206
It's so important that you check your level.

00:53:26.206 --> 00:53:27.400
Where are you?

00:53:27.400 --> 00:53:28.720
Are you ankle deep?

00:53:28.720 --> 00:53:30.400
Are you waist deep?

00:53:30.400 --> 00:53:31.947
Are you knee deep?

00:53:31.947 --> 00:53:33.560
Are you over the head?

00:53:33.560 --> 00:53:42.530
Are you swimming at the bottom wherever Jesus is?

00:53:42.530 --> 00:53:49.853
Are you drinking that living water?

00:53:51.333 --> 00:53:52.646
Or are you stagnant?

00:54:10.606 --> 00:54:10.869
Have you become weary in well-doing?

00:54:10.869 --> 00:54:12.180
Are you backslidden?

00:54:12.180 --> 00:54:13.480
Are you cold?

00:54:13.480 --> 00:54:22.650
The Bible said he would rather you be hot or cold, but if you're lukewarm, he would speu you out of his mouth.

00:54:22.650 --> 00:54:26.840
There's so many people that are living in compromise right now.

00:54:37.091 --> 00:54:37.314
And as I've been listening to this young lady—I don't know her name, she was an ex-witch.

00:54:37.314 --> 00:54:44.830
She got born again and Jesus visited her as she was doing some kind of occultic practice.

00:54:44.830 --> 00:54:48.496
She gave her heart to Christ.

00:54:48.496 --> 00:54:52.624
She's telling everybody how to anoint their house with oil.

00:55:06.710 --> 00:55:07.025
I was so excited that this young woman was teaching people how to anoint their house with oil as an ex-witch.

00:55:07.025 --> 00:55:11.450
The Lord said, "Brendon, I'm coming after the occult.

00:55:11.450 --> 00:55:13.017
I'm coming after the witches.

00:55:13.017 --> 00:55:16.760
I'm coming after the warlocks.

00:55:16.760 --> 00:55:19.545
I'm coming after the seance people.

00:55:20.455 --> 00:55:20.636
" I love them.

00:55:45.120 --> 00:55:45.460
I want all of them to get born again and none should perish.

00:55:45.460 --> 00:55:56.942
So when I hear about this girl, Craft to Christ—whoever, I believe is her channel name—she said, "I gave my heart to Jesus.

00:55:56.942 --> 00:56:01.230
" Now I don't know everything she says.

00:56:12.360 --> 00:56:12.927
I don't know if I agree with everything because I haven't listened to everything.

00:56:22.747 --> 00:56:33.880
But for some of the things she's talking about—anointing the house with oil and standing on the blood with the authority of the blood and the power of the name of Jesus—I got excited about.

00:56:33.880 --> 00:56:35.720
At least she's teaching people.

00:56:42.985 --> 00:56:43.200
A lot of the church doesn't teach anything nowadays about the authority of this bottle of oil.

00:56:44.000 --> 00:56:46.000
I carry this; I've got them everywhere.

00:56:46.000 --> 00:56:49.920
I've got oil in my bedroom.

00:56:49.920 --> 00:56:50.720
I've got oil everywhere.

00:57:05.834 --> 00:57:06.393
All different kinds.

